title: The Life Of Charlotte Bronte Volume 1
creator: Elizabeth Cleghorn Gaskell
description: LibriVox recording of The Life Of Charlotte Bronte Volume 1 by Elizabeth Cleghorn Gaskell. Charlotte Brontë was a British author, the eldest of the three famous Brontë sisters who have become standards of English literature. She is best known for her novel Jane Eyre, one of the greatest classics of all time. Just two years after Charlotte's death, her friend Elizabeth Gaskell wrote her biography. Want to know more about Charlotte Brontë? If you do, please read this biography. (Summary by Stav Nisser.) The recording of the second half of this biography is in progress. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
